Coloration: In life (
Fig. 1
), head yellow-bronze, upper jaw and anteroproximal part of the upper arm bright yellow; venter, throat, chest, sides of the body, hind limbs and hands brown or black brown. A dark stripe extends from the eyes to the arm insertion. Throat and venter with or without small bluish green blotches; flanks, groin and thighs (anterior and ventral) with or without a few bluish spots. Iris dark brown.

Sexual dimorphism: The most remarkable external characteristics to differentiate adult males and females are the presence of vocal slits. Also, a wider disc on finger III and a smaller SVL was found in males (
Table 2
); however, there are a few data to be confident with this sexual difference. Testes and eggs are dark brown.
